Citations
Date: 0/0/1937
Source: Dictionary of Slang
Author: PARTRIDGE
Vol / Page: 609
Edition:
Quote: <i>Pat Malone</i>. Alone: Australian and New Zealand rhyming s.: C. 20. Gen <i>do a thing, go, on one's Pat Malone</i>, hence <i>on one's Pat</i> (hence <i>pat</i>).
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1949
Source: Dictionary of the Underworld
Author: PARTRIDGE
Vol / Page: 498
Edition:
Quote: usually shortened to on one's pat; alone: Pacific coast: C. 20. M and B, 1944. Rhyming slang introduced by Australians.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1984
Source: Outside In
Author: BEATON
Vol / Page: 79
Edition:
Quote: DI: Scared you might spend the Festive Season on Your Pat Malone? <i>Ibid</i>. Glossary 110 <i>to be alone. </i>
